Section 1:
1 L.D. 1981
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 776, L.D. 1981, “An Act to Implement
10 the Recommendations of the Emergency Medical Services' Board and the Blue Ribbon
11 Commission to Study Emergency Medical Services in the State”
12 Amend the bill in section 17 in §90-A in subsection 9 in the 5th line (page 7, line 41 in
13 L.D.) by striking out the following: "an" and inserting the following: 'a mental'
14 Amend the bill in section 17 in §90-A in subsection 9 in the 9th line (page 7, line 45 in
15 L.D.) by inserting after the following: "patients." the following: 'The licensing board may
16 direct an emergency medical services person to submit to a physical examination whenever
17 the licensing board determines the emergency medical services person may have
18 diminished physical capabilities to an extent that they are preventing the emergency
19 medical services person from practicing competently and with safety to patients.'
20 Amend the bill by inserting after section 24 the following:
21 'Sec. 25. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
23 PUBLIC SAFETY, DEPARTMENT OF
24 Emergency Medical Services 0485
25 Initiative: Provides funding for travel reimbursement, Attorney General office
26 representation and expert witness fees related to the newly created Emergency Medical
27 Services Licensing Board.
28 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
29 All Other $0 $20,000
30 __________ __________
31 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $0 $20,000
3228 '
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR0301(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 776, L.D. 1981
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment allows the proposed Emergency Medical Services Licensing Board
33 to direct an emergency medical services person to submit to a physical exam if the board
44 determines the emergency medical services person has diminished physical capabilities to
55 the extent the person cannot practice competently and with safety to patients.
66 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
77 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0301(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
